<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>zf.sh wasn't working for me on Solaris 10 using v1.10.8.</p>

<p>There are two issues...</p>

<p>First of all sh in Solaris 10 isn't bash, so I changed it to use /bin/bash, this would probably be safer across more OS's.
Line 1, change #!/bin/sh to #!/bin/bash</p>

<p>Second there is no readlink on Solaris, I put a separate file in the directory to emulate readlink for Solaris:
--- readlink ---</p>

<h1>!/bin/bash</h1>

<p>cd -P -- "$(dirname -- "$1")" &amp;&amp;
if test -L $1; then
  printf '%s\n' "$(pwd -P)/$(basename "$1")"
fi</p>

<p>Perhaps this could be made into a function within the main zf.sh and not be dependent on readlink.</p>

<p>Alec</p>

